Trans Nzoia Governor Patrick Khaemba has said the county requires more than 24,710 acres (10,000 hectares) to expand Kitale town.He wants the national government to help his administration acquire land from the Kenya Forest Service and the Prisons in the area. The town is so squeezed and we no longer have land to put up public facilities like schools, Khaemba said. He spoke in Kobos, Kwanza constituency, during the launch of the rural electrification programme on...... Deputy President William Ruto was present. Khaemba said Kitale town was planned for a population of less than 50,000 people during colonial days yet the population had grown to more than 350,000.